remarks.para:
       Detailed Description:

       Returns the value of the provided environment variable. 

       If the .env file has the following definitions:

   varX = ";;abc;;";
   varX = "$varX" + ";xyz;;;";
   varZ = "C:\ABCD\DEF    ;" + "   ;C:\XYZ\DEF;" + "d:\EYC";
   varZZ = "C:\ABCD\DEF gh   ;" + "   ;C:\XYZ jj\DEF;" + "d:\EYC";
   varZZZ = "C:\ABCD\DEF gh;" + "C:\XYZ jj\DEF;" + "d:\EYC;" + "e:\jdf\;f:\kef;g:\kexy";



The hdmtAPI will return the following:

   varX will return "abc;xyz"
   varZ will return "C:\ABCD\DEF;C:\XYZ\DEF;d:\EYC"
   varZZ will return "C:\ABCD\DEF gh;C:\XYZ jj\DEF;d:\EYC"
   varZZ will return "C:\ABCD\DEF gh;C:\XYZ jj\DEF;d:\EYC;e:\jdf\;f:\kef;g:\kexy"

